UID:10022291-1772888400-1772899200@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:Fix-it Fair
DESCRIPTION:Bring your broken items to the Fix-it Fair. The PNA Fixers will diagnose and repair your item for free (parts may be extra) while also helping reduce waste in Seattle. At the same time\, you can bond with the rest of your local community and learn something new by watching the repair. Typical items include heaters\, sewing machines\, waffle irons\, blenders\, mixers\, electric bikes\, extension cords\, lamps\, audio gear\, and more. There are hardware stores nearby if you need to fetch parts. There is also a professional knife sharpener on hand\, and we expect to have sewists to mend and hem clothing. Walk-ins are welcome but it’s helpful if you can RSVP to let us know what you’re bringing: bit.ly/GreenwoodFix-itFair. The PNA Fixers meet regularly at Greenwood Hardware on the first Wednesday of every month\, 3–6 pm. \nFree\, but donations are appreciated. \n 
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/fix-it-fair/
LOCATION:Greenwood Senior Center\, 525 N. 85th St.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Events,GSC Featured,Senior Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/05090717/D3A0344.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Greenwood Senior Center":MAILTO:gsc@phinneycenter.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260307T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260307T220000
DTSTAMP:20260307T142900
CREATED:20260206T193741Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260206T193753Z
UID:10030895-1772911800-1772920800@www.phinneycenter.org
SUMMARY:Kristian Bugge & Ruthie Dornfeld – 2 Fiddle masters play Danish & American music and more!
DESCRIPTION:Kristian Bugge (Denmark) and Ruthie Dornfeld (Seattle) will entertain us with a wide range of music including Danish traditional fiddle tunes and music from the other Nordic countries to old-time American and self-composed original tunes\, spiced up with a few Venezuelan waltzes.\nKristian and Ruthie first met each other in the Danish folk music circles in the mid-1990’s\, where Ruthie had been touring regularly and growing a reputation as a well-renowned artist and fiddler since the early 1980’s. Later when Kristian was a music student\, Ruthie was guest-teaching at the Carl Nielsen Academy of Music in Odense\, Denmark and Kristian made sure to take the opportunity to study with her while she was there. About ten years later they met again in and around Seattle when Kristian had started touring and performing in the states. This summer marked a new chapter in their collaboration and friendship as they started touring and recording as a duo for the first time. Expect everything from wild polkas and jigs to lyrical waltzes\, fiery reels and happy hopsas\, all served with humor and stories from their many years on the road. The doors open at 7pm for the 7:30 cocnert in the phinney Community Hall (lower Brick Building). Advance tickets are $26/$24 members of SFS\, PNA\, or Skandia\, students\, or seniors 65+/ $10 Youth to age 17; at the door $2 more for adults ($28/$26/$10).
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/kristian-bugge-ruthie-dornfeld-2-fiddle-masters-play-danish-american-music-and-more/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\, Seattle\, WA\, 98103\, United States
CATEGORIES:Renter Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://media.phinneycenter.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/06113755/Bugge-Dornfeld-1536x1536-1.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Seattle Folklore Society Concerts":MAILTO:concerts@seafolklore.org
END:VEVENT
